name: Oracle Eloqua
description: Add an Eloqua Instance to connect your existing Eloqua account to the Marketing Hub, allowing you to manage accounts, campaigns, contacts etc. across multiple Marketing Elements. You will need your Eloqua account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have a Eloqua account, you can create one at Eloquq Registration

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Endpoint Determination URL
configuration.description: Used to determine Eloqua API endpoint URL

configuration.name: Base URL
configuration.description: Used as Eloqua API base URL to call REST methods

configuration.name: Synchronize
configuration.description: Used to periodically synchronize with Eloqua

configuration.name: Synchronization Interval
configuration.description: The synchronization interval in milliseconds. Defaults to 5 minutes if left empty and the Synchronize property is checked.

configuration.name: Bulk API Base URL
configuration.description: The Eloqua Bulk API Base URL for this account.

configuration.name: Data API Base URL
configuration.description: The Eloqua Data API Base URL for this account.

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

configuration.name: Custom Object Map
configuration.description: Used for storing Custom Objects that are created and the associated ids

Find contacts in the Marketing Automation system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all contacts whose name contains the word 'data', the search expression parameter will be where=name like '%data%'. If a value of true is specified for the includeDeleted flag, then any soft-deleted records will also be considered in the searched records.
